    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-15T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-15T08:00:00-05:00" n="150"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5 Submarines/18: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-15T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 15, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 15—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>399. My despatch 2423, August 6.<note n="4" xml:id="d150fn4">Not printed.</note>
                    The Foreign Office states that the French Government has now arranged to
                    despatch its note in connection with the submarine protocol on the 15th of
                    August to the diplomatic representatives in Paris of the agreements concerned.
                    The date had been postponed from August 10 to August 15 at British <pb
                        facs="0243" n="163" xml:id="pg_163"/> suggestion to give the Italian
                    Government further opportunity to express its views on text of the protocol and
                    general procedure. The Italian Government not having replied, the British
                    consider it impossible to press the French to defer any longer the despatch of
                    their note.</p>
                <p>The Italian Foreign Office has, however, advised the British Embassy in Rome that
                    it hopes shortly to deliver a favorable reply to the British representations in
                    connection with the submarine protocol.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
